posts.name: Ezra
posts.cooked: I’m testing new vision logic on my robot. I decided to update PV on my Orange Pi 5 and in my code to the latest dev version (dev-v2024.3.0-70-g24fb6af5) and now it is no longer showing the results from the camera in the code. on photonvision.local:5800 it shows the april tag just fine, but the result in my code shows no visible tags. The camera name is set correctly and I didn’t change anything in the code before it stopped working.

posts.name: Owen Busler
posts.cooked: Can you look at the raw network tables values? Is PV pushing values to the tables which are in a different format so your code isnt picking them up, or is nothing being put on the network tables. If you roll back to 2024.3.1 does it work?

Is there a reason you updated to latest dev? In the off season this isn’t really meant to be stable and may be broken (unless this isn’t a bug / some config error). I’d recommend using a stable version unless you need something that’s in the new version.

posts.name: John Fogarty
posts.cooked: The best place to provide feedback on development builds of PV is their discord server I would imagine.

As mentioned above, the best place for support is the pv discord. I know at least the network tables structure for a target was changed between now and 2024.3.1, which is probably causing an issue if you don’t have new vendor deps. PV is also built with the wpilib alpha so the vendor dep might not be compatible with the code you are working on.

posts.name: Ezra
posts.cooked: I tried asking there, no one helped me.

posts.name: Ezra
posts.cooked: I don’t fully understand what you’re trying to say. I updated to the correct version of PhotonLib in my code as well

posts.cooked: If I did looked at it correctly, it is updating the values in the NT but it’s not trying to get those values in the code. I didn’t update the code when I updated the version except for changing a couple things with getMultiTagResult because it changed in the library. (Like changing result.getMultiTagResult().estimatedPose.isPresent to result.getMultiTagResult().isPresent() )
